<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP18_AdvancedTattooTools" s="440927">
  <T n="category">420278<!--tutorial_Category_EP18_Obsession--></T>
  <T n="name">0x4DB8F660<!--Advanced Tattoo Tools--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_AdvancedTattooing_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a0ffb4fdfd5f156d</T>
      <T n="text">0x6B9C1B14<!--Tattoos have received a glow up! Use the <b><font color='#199C2C'>advanced Tattoo tools</font></b> in Create a Sim to make truly custom Tattoo creations. Your Sim’s ink has never looked this good!\n\nThese tools can be accessed by Offering or Requesting a Custom Tattoo via a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Tattoo Table</font></b>, or simply by <b><font color='#199C2C'>entering Create a Sim</font></b> normally, for example using a Mirror or Dresser, and selecting <b><font color='#199C2C'>Tattoos</font></b> in the Body menu.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_AdvancedTattooing_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a0ffb4fdfd5f156e</T>
      <T n="text">0x52FB3E4F<!--Tattoo Designs can now be <b><font color='#199C2C'>layered</font></b>, with up to five Designs in the same slot. Use the layer menu to add or remove layers, change the order of layers, and select which layer to edit.\n\nDon’t forget to use the <b><font color='#199C2C'>sliders</font></b> on the Tattoo Designs to customize them further. You can edit their opacity, and for some Designs, you can even adjust hue, saturation, and brightness!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_AdvancedTattooing_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a0ffb4fdfd5f156f</T>
      <T n="text">0xB281297F<!--Every slot can also be edited in <b><font color='#199C2C'>Paint Mode</font></b> with Stamps, Stencils, and Brushes. This creates a custom Tattoo layer that is always at the top of the layer order.\n\nWhile in Paint Mode, you can only edit the <b><font color='#199C2C'>current slot</font></b>. Use the button to highlight your current slot to make it easier to see its boundaries. To edit <b><font color='#199C2C'>another slot</font></b>, go back to the regular Tattoos menu, select another slot, and enter Paint Mode from there.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_AdvancedTattooing_Slide4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a0ffb4fdfd5f1568</T>
      <T n="text">0x6B2651B4<!--Use <b><font color='#199C2C'>Stamps</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Brushes</font></b> to stamp and draw unique designs on your Sims. Edit the color, opacity, size, and rotation of the Stamp or Brush for the perfect effect.\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Stencils</font></b> allow you to draw, similar to a Brush, but within the lines of a specific design. If you want, you can combine different stencils by drawing with one first, and then another!--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP18\UI\Tutorial\EP18_Lesson_AdvancedTattooing_Slide5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a0ffb4fdfd5f1569</T>
      <T n="text">0x503ACD4B<!--Last but not least, you can save your Tattoo creations to the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Library</font></b> and upload them to the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Gallery</font></b>! Just use the Save button in the layer menu. This saves all layers in the current slot, including anything added in Paint Mode, as a Tattoo creation.\n\nBrowse the Gallery’s Tattoo category to find Tattoo creations made by others!--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
